  "review": {
    "status": "reviewed",
    "reviewed_at": "2026-05-22T22:37:52",
    "reviewer": "agent",
    "summary": "This paper presents new V-band photopolarimetric measurements of the semi-regular variable V CVn over three pulsation cycles (2020-2022), identifies analogue sources (L2 Pup, UZ Ari, AK Peg, RX Boo, Z UMa), and discusses models for the polarization variability. Data assets include: (1) 5 journal tables of original photopolarimetric measurements (JD, P_cal, PA_cal, Q_cal, U_cal with errors, mag(V) with errors, exposure time, observer) totaling 227 measurements over 227 nights; (2) one compilation table of 6 V CVn-type stars with literature stellar parameters; (3) two calibration tables (unpolarized standards, highly polarized standards); (4) one derived interstellar polarization estimate. Raw data also hosted on Zenodo (https://zenodo.org/record/7997101). External resources include Gaia mission acknowledgements. The journal tables (AppendB) are the primary original data product."
  },
